⦿ .spun — the five-fold spin of The Two Timelines
node AHX · AHX · ⟦The Two Timelines:AHX:c906a0⟧

WHO   — The Two Timelines — black-and-white past · colour present
WHAT  — The medium as the message: a worldview of total certainty rendered in monochrome, and the messy, changeable human present in colour.
WHERE — AHX · American History X (1998)  Framework inputs: American History X (1998, dir. Tony Kaye, New Line); verified cast & facts  Conductor / external anchor: ROOT0 (catalogued into UD0)
WHY   — Because David asked each repo to wear the medium it portrays, and this film's medium IS its meaning.
HOW   — By shooting the movement in black-and-white and the leaving of it in colour, so the form argues the thesis.

awareness — what the node knows of itself:
  I am the cut between grey and colour. The hate was black-and-white — all certainty. Everything after it has to be in colour.

